Package com.groq.sdk.models.chat

Class ChatCompletionRequest

java.lang.Object
com.groq.sdk.models.chat.ChatCompletionRequest
public class ChatCompletionRequest extends Object
Represents a request for chat completion to the Groq API. Contains all parameters for generating chat responses including model selection, message history, tool definitions, and generation parameters.

Example usage:


 ChatMessage message = new ChatMessage("user", "Hello, how are you?");
 ChatCompletionRequest request = new ChatCompletionRequest("openai/gpt-oss-20b", List.of(message));
 request.setMaxTokens(100);
 request.setTemperature(0.7);

Example usage with tools:


 ChatMessage message = new ChatMessage("user", "What's the weather in San Francisco?");
 ChatCompletionRequest request = new ChatCompletionRequest("llama-3.1-8b-instant", List.of(message));
 
 // Define a tool
 FunctionDefinition function = new FunctionDefinition("get_weather", "Get weather for a location");
 ChatTool tool = new ChatTool("function", function);
 request.setTools(List.of(tool));
 request.setToolChoice("auto");

    • getToolChoice

      public Object getToolChoice()
      Gets the tool choice configuration. Controls which (if any) tool is called by the model. `none` means the model will not call any tool and instead generates a message. `auto` means the model can pick between generating a message or calling one or more tools. `required` means the model must call one or more tools. Specifying a particular tool via `ChatNamedToolChoice` forces the model to call that tool. `none` is the default when no tools are present. `auto` is the default if tools are present.
      Returns:
      the tool choice, or null if not set

    • setToolChoice

      public void setToolChoice(Object toolChoice)
      Sets the tool choice configuration. Controls which (if any) tool is called by the model. `none` means the model will not call any tool and instead generates a message. `auto` means the model can pick between generating a message or calling one or more tools. `required` means the model must call one or more tools. Specifying a particular tool via `ChatNamedToolChoice` forces the model to call that tool. `none` is the default when no tools are present. `auto` is the default if tools are present.
      Parameters:
      toolChoice - the tool choice (String or ChatNamedToolChoice)
